<item>
            <title>[LU-19664] kernel update [RHEL 10.1 6.12.0-124.20.1.el10_1]</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19664</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Security Fix(es) for kernel 6.12.0-124.16.1.el10_1:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;kernel: ublk: make sure ubq-&amp;gt;canceling is set when queue is frozen (CVE-2025-22068)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;kernel: nfsd: handle get_client_locked() failure in nfsd4_setclientid_confirm() (CVE-2025-38724)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;kernel: mm/memory-failure: fix VM_BUG_ON_PAGE(PagePoisoned(page)) when unpoison memory (CVE-2025-39883)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;kernel: e1000e: fix heap overflow in e1000_set_eeprom (CVE-2025-39898)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;kernel: wifi: mt76: fix linked list corruption (CVE-2025-39918)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;kernel: i40e: fix idx validation in config queues msg (CVE-2025-39971)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://access.redhat.com/errata/product/479/ver=/rhel---10/x86_64/RHSA-2025:22395&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://access.redhat.com/errata/product/479/ver=/rhel---10/x86_64/RHSA-2025:22395&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Security Fix(es) for kernel 6.12.0-124.20.1.el10_1:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;kernel: cifs: Fix oops due to uninitialised variable (CVE-2025-38737)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;kernel: can: j1939: implement NETDEV_UNREGISTER notification handler (CVE-2025-39925)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;kernel: Bluetooth: hci_event: Fix UAF in hci_acl_create_conn_sync (CVE-2025-39982)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;kernel: Bluetooth: MGMT: Fix possible UAFs (CVE-2025-39981)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;kernel: net/mlx5: fs, fix UAF in flow counter release (CVE-2025-39979)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;kernel: Bluetooth: hci_event: Fix UAF in hci_conn_tx_dequeue (CVE-2025-39983)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;kernel: io_uring/waitid: always prune wait queue entry in io_waitid_wait() (CVE-2025-40047)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;kernel: iommu/vt-d: Disallow dirty tracking if incoherent page walk (CVE-2025-40058)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;kernel: ice: ice_adapter: release xa entry on adapter allocation failure (CVE-2025-40185)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://access.redhat.com/errata/product/479/ver=/rhel---10/x86_64/RHSA-2025:22854&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://access.redhat.com/errata/product/479/ver=/rhel---10/x86_64/RHSA-2025:22854&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
